The project follows a 3-tier branch workflow: feature/* or bugfix/* → dev → main.

- feature/* and bugfix/* branches are always created from dev, never from main.
- All feature/bugfix work is merged into dev first and tested on the dev Docker environment (port 3002) before any further merge.
- dev is merged into main only when a set of changes is ready to ship as a release.
- main is never committed to directly. It only receives merges from dev.
- Production is deployed by running ./deploy.sh from main, which enforces that local main matches origin/main and that origin/dev is fully merged in.
- Subagents should confirm that the dev Docker container has been rebuilt and tested before any merge into dev or main, and must warn if a user attempts to commit directly to main or merge a feature branch directly into main.
